    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Don't Omit Levinson</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Myron R Ratkowski letter comments on Stephen Holden's April 23 article on onscreen discussions of popular culture (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Stephen Holden's article about on-screen discussions of popular culture [''Admitting to Our Other Obsessions,'' April 23] gave undue credit to Quentin Tarantino in leading the way with ''Reservoir Dogs'' and ''Pulp Fiction.'' The true leader in pop culture conversations found in movies is the writer-director Barry Levinson in ''Tin Men'' and ''Diner.''</p>
        <p>MYRON R. RATKOWSKI  Milwaukee</p>
      </block>
